__________________________region____________________________

~region[...]:  defines a region, in this case we put the whole system
               into one single region 

  \element_top_type{residue} : defines the topology type of the elements
                               e.g. our region is a collection of 6 residues
  
  \nres{.}                   : number of residues within a region 

  \residues{. , ., ...}      : specify the residues by chain:number
                               you could look at the .pdb to get this
                               information

  \ncenter{.}                : the number of rotational center(s) for the 
                               whole region (this is more relevant if you
                               have multiple regions )
  
  \centers{., ., ...}        : specify the rotation center(s) by chain:number

  \nrespair{.}               : number of residue pairs (e.g. a base pair)
  
  \residue_pair{ . , . }     : defines a residue pair by chain:number

  \prop_trans_sig{ }         : the magnitude of the overall translational 
                               move for the whole region in Angstrom
                               (relevant if we have multiple regions)
 
  \prop_rot_sig{ }           : the magnitude of the overall rotational 
                               move for the whole region in radian
                               (relevant if we have multiple regions)
 
  \prop_trans_sig_freeres{}  : the magnitude of translational move of
                               an individual "free" residue contained 
                               in the region. "free" refers to residues 
                               not in any base pair

  \prop_rot_sig_freeres{}   :  the magnitude of rotational move of
                               an individual "free" residue contained 
                               in the region. "free" refers to residues 
                               not in any base pair

  \prop_trans_sig_respair{} : analog move sizes for base pairs 
  \prop_rot_sig_respair{}     base pair
______________________________________________________________________
